untyAwarded","message":"Per the above comment","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003ePer the above comment\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2019-02-23T02:57:50.814Z","updated_at":"2019-02-23T02:57:50.814Z","actor":{"url":"/slack","ibb":false,"profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/069/683fee312381bc46cadc7ea1950abc87944d12c3_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"profile":{"name":"Slack"}},"bounty_amount":"500.0","bounty_currency":"usd","bonus_amount":"0.0","genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"slack","collaborator":{"username":"pclinger","url":"/pclinger"},"actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":4198834,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hello Max,\n\nThank you for the bounty, I appreciate it.\n\nI wanted to get your thoughts on the severity of this issue. On the HackerOne Slack page, it indicates that authentication bugs which affect all teams fall under Tier 0 ($1500+), while bugs affecting a single team would be Tier 2 ($500+).\n\nThis bug affects all teams, so I was curious what the thought process was here.\n\nThanks for your time,\n\nPatrick","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eHello Max,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThank you for the bounty, I appreciate it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI wanted to get your thoughts on the severity of this issue. On the HackerOne Slack page, it indicates that authentication bugs which affect all teams fall under Tier 0 ($1500+), while bugs affecting a single team would be Tier 2 ($500+).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis bug affects all teams, so I was curious what the thought process was here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThanks for your time,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePatrick\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2019-02-24T05:55:50.908Z","updated_at":"2019-02-24T05:55:50.908Z","actor":{"username":"pclinger","cleared":false,"url":"/pclinger","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"slack","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":4948389,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hey @pclinger - so sorry for the delay, and thank you for your patience. When we consider an authentication bug affecting all teams, it refers to a bug which would allow a user on one team to bypass auth for an arbitrary team. So in this case it's a less severe issue because it requires reuse of hardware/physical access to a victim's device, whereas Tier 0 would be something along the lines of \"attacker can access arbitrary accounts on any team\". Does that explain that a bit better? Sorry for the confusion!","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eHey \u003ca href=\"/pclinger\"\u003e@pclinger\u003c/a\u003e - so sorry for the delay, and thank you for your patience. When we consider an authentication bug affecting all teams, it refers to a bug which would allow a user on one team to bypass auth for an arbitrary team. So in this case it\u0026#39;s a less severe issue because it requires reuse of hardware/physical access to a victim\u0026#39;s device, whereas Tier 0 would be something along the lines of \u0026quot;attacker can access arbitrary accounts on any team\u0026quot;. Does that explain that a bit better? Sorry for the confusion!\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2019-05-29T12:06:43.344Z","updated_at":"2019-05-29T12:06:43.344Z","actor":{"username":"maxfeldman","cleared":false,"url":"/maxfeldman","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/016/613/37b54dbac5da0a42db471713959c8bf2de89a12d_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackeron